text: Tanumshede is an urban area in the county of Västra Götaland in Sweden. It is the seat of Tanum Municipality. The Rock Carvings in Tanum are a collection of petroglyphs near Tanumshede. They were declared a World Heritage Site by UNESCO in 1994. In total there are thousands of images on about 600 panels. == References == ==Other websites== Category:Settlements in Vastra Gotaland County Category:World Heritage Sites in Sweden
